"{\"uid\": \"countrylife.co.uk-food-drink-bay-watch-why-laurel-leaves-have-done-everything-from-crown-emperors-and-olympic-champions-to-flavouring-stews-272065\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Not many plants can claim a place both on the haughty brow of an emperor and in the humble stew pot, says Ian Morton, as he looks at the laurel tree.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 106, \"end\": 116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Morton\", \"score\": 0.9999767845550189, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ian Morton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Morton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ian_Morton\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Not many plants\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 15}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 26, \"to\": 33}, {\"ngram\": \"the haughty brow\", \"from\": 42, \"to\": 58}, {\"ngram\": \"an emperor\", \"from\": 62, \"to\": 72}, {\"ngram\": \"the humble stew pot\", \"from\": 80, \"to\": 99}, {\"ngram\": \"the laurel tree\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 148}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hail Caesar!\", \"from\": 151, \"to\": 163, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hail Caesar\", \"from\": 151, \"to\": 162}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The imperial brow was adorned as usual by a laurel wreath, for only the most prestigious Roman personages were granted the symbol of excellence, the leafy crown.\", \"from\": 164, \"to\": 325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 253, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.9999999881165423, \"rank\": 1.1254105746629973e-08, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The imperial brow\", \"from\": 164, \"to\": 181}, {\"ngram\": \"a laurel wreath\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 221}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 293}, {\"ngram\": \"excellence\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 307}, {\"ngram\": \"the leafy crown\", \"from\": 309, \"to\": 324}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ever fearful of treachery in those days of shifting allegiances, he had faith that laurel would live up to its reputation of offering protection against all manner of misfortune, seen and unseen.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 521, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"treachery\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"those days\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 365}, {\"ngram\": \"allegiances\", \"from\": 378, \"to\": 389}, {\"ngram\": \"faith\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 403}, {\"ngram\": \"laurel\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"its reputation\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"protection\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 470}, {\"ngram\": \"all manner\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 489}, {\"ngram\": \"misfortune\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 503}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among its guardian virtues, laurel would never be struck by lightning.\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 592, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its guardian virtues\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"laurel\", \"from\": 550, \"to\": 556}, {\"ngram\": \"lightning\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In that respect, as far as we know, it worked for all the Caesars other than Marcus Aurelius Carus, emperor in AD282-83, who was reportedly felled when campaigning against the Sassanid empire, now Iran.\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 670, \"end\": 676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.684374944772865e-43, \"text\": \"Marcus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\"}, {\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8486193210494372e-19, \"text\": \"Carus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carus\"}, {\"begin\": 769, \"end\": 777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasanian_Empire\", \"score\": 0.9999999999836291, \"rank\": 1.6263250618705255e-11, \"text\": \"Sassanid\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasanian_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasanian_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 790, \"end\": 794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greater_Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999998576995596, \"rank\": 7.403807721783981e-08, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greater_Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greater_Iran\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that respect\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 608}, {\"ngram\": \"all the Caesars\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"emperor\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 700}, {\"ngram\": \"AD282\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 709}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was probably wearing a metal helmet instead of his wreath.\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 857, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a metal helmet\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 834}, {\"ngram\": \"his wreath\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whence did the formidable power of laurel in the classical era originate?\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 932, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the formidable power\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 890}, {\"ngram\": \"laurel\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 900}, {\"ngram\": \"the classical era originate\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Native to the Mediterranean region and one of the oldest trees to be cultivated, it became sacred to the god Apollo - he of sun, truth, prophecy, poetry, music, dance and healing.\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 1112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1042, \"end\": 1048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.419097801313993e-40, \"text\": \"Apollo\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Mediterranean region\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 967}, {\"ngram\": \"the oldest trees\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 995}, {\"ngram\": \"the god\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1041}, {\"ngram\": \"sun\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"truth\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"prophecy\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"poetry\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"dance\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1099}, {\"ngram\": \"healing\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1111}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Worshipped in both ancient Athens and Rome, in Greek mythology he was pursuing the water nymph Daphne, who avoided his lecherous advances by turning, with her father's help, into a laurel tree (the modern Greek word for which isdaphne).\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1140, \"end\": 1146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classical_Athens\", \"score\": 0.8094259080161434, \"rank\": 0.19574418188938442, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classical_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classical_Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 1151, \"end\": 1155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.9999999979145286, \"rank\": 2.085315955918227e-09, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 1160, \"end\": 1175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5586185683214921e-28, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 1208, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daphne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8188600876672473e-28, \"text\": \"Daphne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daphne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daphne\"}, {\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.4920988282162854, \"rank\": 0.7152805031170787, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his lecherous advances\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1250}, {\"ngram\": \"her father's help\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"a laurel tree\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1305}, {\"ngram\": \"isdaphne\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So deep was Apollo's frustration and affection that he adopted the laurel and endowed it with special qualities, its wreaths a symbol of wisdom, courage and strength, awarded to the highest achievers: poets, orators, statesmen, doctors, athletes and warrior heroes (it remains ill-advised to rest on one's laurels).\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.419097801313993e-40, \"text\": \"Apollo\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"affection\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1399}, {\"ngram\": \"the laurel\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"special qualities\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1464}, {\"ngram\": \"its wreaths\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1477}, {\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1486}, {\"ngram\": \"wisdom\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1496}, {\"ngram\": \"courage\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"strength\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest achievers\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"poets\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1559}, {\"ngram\": \"orators\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1568}, {\"ngram\": \"statesmen\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1579}, {\"ngram\": \"doctors\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"warrior heroes\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1617}, {\"ngram\": \"one's laurels\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Successful students of the era were crowned with wreaths of laurel berries, the Latin for which isbaccalaureus, and our poets laureate likewise inherit an ancient literary honour.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1729, \"end\": 1735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurus_nobilis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.060414616114586e-19, \"text\": \"laurel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurus_nobilis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurus_nobilis\"}, {\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2752116290767086e-20, \"text\": \"Latin\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Successful students\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1688}, {\"ngram\": \"the era\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"wreaths\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1725}, {\"ngram\": \"our poets\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1794}, {\"ngram\": \"an ancient literary honour\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We know the laurel familiarly as the bay - tree and bush - distinctive, decorative and evergreen, with leaves that add a subtle savour to dishes.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1995, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the laurel\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"the bay - tree\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"leaves\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"a subtle savour\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"dishes\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 1994}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is ironic that the bay is named not for its foliage, but for its fruit, from Old Frenchbaie, a berry.\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2100, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bay\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2021}, {\"ngram\": \"its foliage\", \"from\": 2039, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"its fruit\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"Old Frenchbaie\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2090}, {\"ngram\": \"a berry\", \"from\": 2092, \"to\": 2099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A further twist.\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2117, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A further twist\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thanks to the Linnaeus classification of 1758, horticulture knows the bay asLaurus nobilis:laurwas Celtic for green and the 'noble' element sprang from the Greco-Roman heroic culture.\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2301, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Linnaeus classification\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2155}, {\"ngram\": \"horticulture\", \"from\": 2165, \"to\": 2177}, {\"ngram\": \"the bay asLaurus nobilis\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'noble' element\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"the Greco-Roman heroic culture\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The evergreen had a mystical side - Romans loved their omens.\", \"from\": 2303, \"to\": 2364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2339, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.9999999944011506, \"rank\": 5.5986900644612924e-09, \"text\": \"Romans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The evergreen\", \"from\": 2303, \"to\": 2316}, {\"ngram\": \"a mystical side\", \"from\": 2321, \"to\": 2336}, {\"ngram\": \"their omens\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2363}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Historian Suetonius recorded that a laurel grove planted by Empress Livia and used exclusively for wreaths wilted and died unaccountably just before Nero was assassinated, bringing an unpleasant dynasty to an end.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2375, \"end\": 2384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suetonius\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.109789295768353e-20, \"text\": \"Suetonius\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suetonius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suetonius\"}, {\"begin\": 2433, \"end\": 2438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Livia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.671190713844487e-37, \"text\": \"Livia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Livia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Livia\"}, {\"begin\": 2514, \"end\": 2518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nero\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3629367277869125e-44, \"text\": \"Nero\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nero\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nero\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wreaths\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2471}, {\"ngram\": \"an unpleasant dynasty\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2567}, {\"ngram\": \"an end\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Branches were burned in Delphic rites and the narcotic and stimulating effects of the leaves meant priestesses chewed them before pronouncing prophecies.\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2732, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Branches\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2587}, {\"ngram\": \"Delphic rites\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2616}, {\"ngram\": \"the narcotic and stimulating effects\", \"from\": 2621, \"to\": 2657}, {\"ngram\": \"the leaves\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"priestesses\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2689}, {\"ngram\": \"prophecies\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The belief that bay leaves under the pillow could evoke dreams foretelling the future survived in medieval folklore, particularly among maidens seeking guidance in their quest for true love.\", \"from\": 2733, \"to\": 2923, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The belief\", \"from\": 2733, \"to\": 2743}, {\"ngram\": \"bay\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2752}, {\"ngram\": \"the pillow\", \"from\": 2766, \"to\": 2776}, {\"ngram\": \"dreams\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2818}, {\"ngram\": \"medieval folklore\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 2848}, {\"ngram\": \"maidens\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 2876}, {\"ngram\": \"guidance\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2893}, {\"ngram\": \"their quest\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 2908}, {\"ngram\": \"true love\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 2922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bay also held great medicinal value.\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 2961, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bay\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 2928}, {\"ngram\": \"great medicinal value\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2960}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Roman naturalist Pliny prescribed a bay infusion to treat paralysis, sciatica, bruising, headaches, spasms and throat and ear infections.\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 3099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2962, \"end\": 2967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.9999999881165423, \"rank\": 1.1254105746629973e-08, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bay infusion\", \"from\": 2996, \"to\": 3010}, {\"ngram\": \"paralysis\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3029}, {\"ngram\": \"sciatica\", \"from\": 3031, \"to\": 3039}, {\"ngram\": \"bruising\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3049}, {\"ngram\": \"headaches\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3060}, {\"ngram\": \"spasms\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3068}, {\"ngram\": \"throat\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3079}, {\"ngram\": \"ear\", \"from\": 3084, \"to\": 3087}, {\"ngram\": \"infections\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In bath water, it eased rheumatic pain.\", \"from\": 3100, \"to\": 3139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bath water\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3113}, {\"ngram\": \"rheumatic pain\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Medieval practices sustained its worth.\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Medieval practices\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3158}, {\"ngram\": \"its worth\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3178}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Culpeper advocated that distillations should be rubbed on sprains, used as ear drops and declared them 'effectual against the poisons of all venomous creatures and the sting of wasps and bees'.\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3373, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Culpeper\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3188}, {\"ngram\": \"distillations\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3217}, {\"ngram\": \"sprains\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3245}, {\"ngram\": \"ear drops\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3264}, {\"ngram\": \"the poisons\", \"from\": 3302, \"to\": 3313}, {\"ngram\": \"all venomous creatures\", \"from\": 3317, \"to\": 3339}, {\"ngram\": \"the sting\", \"from\": 3344, \"to\": 3353}, {\"ngram\": \"wasps\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3362}, {\"ngram\": \"bees\", \"from\": 3367, \"to\": 3371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Traditional medicine suggested benefits to breathing and digestion, as well as the stimulation of appetite and hair growth.\", \"from\": 3374, \"to\": 3497, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Traditional medicine\",